    <text id="B0123T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Jackson asks after Hannah Collins, the wife of David Collins, from whom he has
                    not heard since she left to visit family in Winchester. McDonnell's attached
                    endorsement reports that Hannah Collins is now living with another man in
                    Winchester.</p>
            </div1>
            <div1 type="addenda" id="d4">
                <p>Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">R.F. &amp;
                    A.L.</abbr>, <abbr expan="Headquarters">HeadQrs</abbr> 9th Sub <abbr
                        expan="District">Dist.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr>, Winchester, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr>.
                        <abbr expan="August">Aug.</abbr> 31/67<lb/>Respectfully returned to Mr. <hi
                        rend="underline">Thos. P. Jackson</hi>, Agent. Hannah Collins is now here
                    living with <hi rend="underline">George W. Grey</hi>, <abbr expan="colored"
                        >col'd</abbr>, as his wife.<lb/>John A. McDonnell, <abbr
                        expan="Captain and Sub Assistant Commissioner">Capt. &amp;
                SAC</abbr></p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d5">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d6">
                <head>
                    Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands,<lb/>Office 4th Division, 9th
                    Sub-District, Virginia
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Captain">Capt.</abbr> John A.
                        McDonnell<lb/>Sub <abbr expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst
                        Comr</abbr><lb/>Winchester</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-08-28"><abbr expan="August">Aug</abbr> 28 1867</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Captain</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>David Collins (<abbr expan="colored">c</abbr>) asks that enquiry be made at
                    Winchester for his wife Hannah Collins (Reed) who left Staunton in September
                    1866, with the intention of visiting her mother <unclear>Larmia</unclear> Smith
                        (<abbr expan="colored">c</abbr>) at Winchester since which time nothing has
                    been heard of her David &amp; Hannah are Registered (No 632) as husband
                    &amp; wife and he is anxious to hear where she is and if alive that she
                    return to her home at West View.</p>

                <p>David has made enquiry himself without success and is not able to make the
                    journey to Winchester. </p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>
                        <abbr expan="Your obedient servant">Yr. obt sevt</abbr>
                    </salute>
                    <signed><hi rend="underline">Tho<hi rend="super">s</hi> P
                    Jackson</hi><lb/>Agent</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
